
Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I go to Page 04 of Elbow MRI

When I select 'Finding' radio button
Then 'Finding' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Fracture' from the dropdown menu
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Localization' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Diaphyseal radius' from 'Localization' dropdown menu
Then '2R2A: Simple fracture' radio button is enabled
And '2R2B: Wedge fracture' radio button is enabled
And '2R2C: Multifragmentary fracture' radio button is enabled
And 'Radial shaft fracture, not further specified' radio button is enabled

When I select '2R2A: Simple fracture' radio button
Then '2R2A1' radio button is enabled
And '2R2A2' radio button is enabled
And '2R2A3' radio button is enabled
And 'a: Proximal third' radio button is enabled
And 'b: Middle third' radio button is enabled
And 'c: Distal third' radio button is enabled

When I select '2R2B: Wedge fracture' radio button
Then '2R2B2' radio button is enabled
And '2R2B3' radio button is enabled
And 'a: Proximal third' radio button is enabled
And 'b: Middle third' radio button is enabled
And 'c: Distal third' radio button is enabled

When I select '2R2C: Multifragmentary fracture' radio button
Then '2R2C2' radio button is enabled
And '2R2C3' radio button is enabled
And 'i: Proximal dia-metaphyseal' radio button is enabled
And 'j: Diaphyseal' radio button is enabled
And 'k: Distal dia-metaphyseal' radio button is enabled


When I select 'Radial shaft fracture, not further specified' radio button
Then 'Fracture older, remodeled' radio button is enabled
And 'Suspected' radio button is enabled
